items.name: Neopets Wiki
items.title: Neopets Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Neopets Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to Neopets Wiki, the Neopets community site that anyone can edit, including you! If you're looking to jump into editing, we have a lot of things that need work, so we strongly encourage you to create missing pages and help us update our current ones. Above all, we're happy to have you here sharing your knowledge and passion for Neopets!

items.name: Religion-wiki
items.title: Religion-wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Religion Wiki
items.desc:
The religion database and community that anyone can edit! All subjects related to religion are within the scope of this wiki, from Buddhism to Judaism to Hinduism.

We cover all sorts of topic, from holy books and literature through to famous people and locations and important imagery and objects.

items.name: The Babylon Project
items.title: The Babylon Project
items.headline: Welcome to the Babylon 5 Wiki!
items.desc:
This wiki is dedicated to the show Babylon 5, which is an American space opera television series created by writer and producer J. Michael Straczynski, under the Babylonian Productions label.

Set between the years 2258 and 2262, it depicts a future where Earth has sovereign states, and a unifying Earthgov. Colonies within the solar system, and beyond, make up the Earth Alliance, and contact has been made with other spacefaring races.

Join our wiki!

items.name: Familypedia
items.title: Familypedia
items.headline: Welcome to Familypedia, the genealogy and family history wiki
items.desc: This is a place where you can create articles about your ancestors, and easily link them to (and from) other articles about their cousins and where and when they lived. The focus of this wiki is on capturing the details of the lives of our ancestors, both those historically significant people and the everyday people usually not listed in encyclopaedias, histories, or even "people's histories". Along the way, the site will also provide information about the historical and social context in which our ancestors found themselves!

items.name: Celebrity Wiki
items.title: Celebrity Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Celebrity wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Celebrity wiki, the online resource about your favourite stars and celebrities that anyone can edit! Here you'll find lots of interesting facts about your favorite celebrities, including things that certain other on-line encyclopedias consider too "trivial". Please feel free to contribute new pages or add to existing ones.

items.name: Alternative History
items.title: Alternative History
items.headline: Alternative History Wiki
items.desc:
Alternate History (sometimes abbreviated AH) is the most frequently used term for the fictional genre which often presupposes a change of a minor historical event that produces an incredible series of changes in the world, diverging it from Our Timeline (OTL) and creating a new, alternate and parallel world.

Here you can create your own Alternate History story, timeline, or add to other existing historical settings. You can start one from the ground up, or add to our many existing variations right down to maps, timelines, and even events.

items.name: Pokémon Wiki
items.title: Pokémon Wiki
items.headline: Pokémon Wiki
items.desc: Pokémon is a multi-media franchise that's owned and developed by the major Japanese games manufacturer, Nintendo. It is second only to the company's Mario Brothers franchise in terms of profitability — making it the world's second most lucrative video game franchise. Pokémon gets its fan base hooked on creature collection — to complete what's called the Pokédex — in order to achieve various goals and to improve their combat abilities. The franchise exists as several video games, a trading card game, televised anime, manga, and even theatrical films.

items.name: Future
items.title: Future
items.headline: Welcome to... the Future!
items.desc: The best way to predict the future, is to create it. ~ Abraham Lincoln

items.name: The Sims Wiki
items.title: The Sims Wiki
items.headline: The Sims Wiki - the ultimate encyclopedia on The Sims
items.desc:
The Sims Wiki was founded in 2005 and is an encyclopedia devoted to The Sims series developed by Maxis and EA Games. With over 7,000 articles as of January 2013, it has a wide array of information for whatever aspect of the series you are looking for. We even have a dedicated namespace for fanon content where you can write about your own character's adventures.

Our community is very welcoming to new users and we have various different social aspects, such as an off-topic forum, Chat, an IRC channel, social media pages, a Steam group amongst other things to engage the community. So why not drop in, check the place out and get involved? Enjoy!

items.name: SGCommand
items.title: SGCommand
items.headline: Stargate Wiki
items.desc: Stargate Wiki is a comprehensive database dedicated to Stargate:SG-1, Stargate:Atlantis, Stargate:Universe, Stargate:Infinity, Stargate Origins, and the Stargate movies, books, and other media. Information covers characters, cast, planets, races, and more.

items.name: DIY Culture
items.title: DIY Culture
items.headline: Welcome to the DIY Culture Wiki
items.desc: Do It Yourself, or DIY, is a term that is used by various communities of practice that focus on people creating things for themselves without the aid of a paid professional. DIY has a lengthy history around the world, since through the ages of camp life, and later village and town life, the most common situation has been for people to use local technologies to take care of their needs for themselves (and, for most of the centuries now past, even to make their own tools, clothing and so on). Check out the wiki now for some great DIY tips!

items.name: Le monde des chemins de fer
items.title: Le monde des chemins de fer

items.name: Cities Wiki
items.title: Cities Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Cities Wikia!
items.desc: This Wikia is designed to display generally positive information about towns and cities — places you've lived, played, or worked. Tell about your favorite spots or give advice for visitors. Let people know about good places to eat, vacation, or play. Talk about schools, people, and societies. Please feel free to contribute!

items.name: Wookieepedia
items.title: Wookieepedia
items.headline: Wookieepedia, the Star Wars Wiki
items.desc: Wookieepedia is an online encyclopedia that contains detailed information about the Star Wars movies and the spin-offs from those, including books and video games.

items.name: The One Wiki to Rule Them All
items.title: The One Wiki to Rule Them All
items.headline: One Wiki to Rule Them All
items.desc: One Wiki to Rule Them All is the definitive knowledge base for the Lord of the Rings books and films as well as anything related to or of J.R.R. Tolkien's fantasy universe of Middle-earth, including role-playing games, video games, and more.

items.name: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.title: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.headline: Welcome to The Firefly and Serenity Database!
items.desc:
Welcome to the encyclopedia based on Joss Whedon's series and film that anyone can edit.

Firefly is a science fiction television series that premiered in the United States and Canada on September 20, 2002. Its naturalistic future setting, modeled after traditional Western movie motifs, presents an atypical science fiction backdrop for the narrative. It was conceived by writer and director Joss Whedon, creator of Buffy the Vampire Slayer and Angel, under his production tag, Mutant Enemy.

Serenity is a 2005 science-fiction film written and directed by Joss Whedon. It is set in the universe of the canceled Fox science fiction television series Firefly, taking place a few months after the events of the final episode.

items.name: Community Central
items.title: Community Central
items.headline: Welcome to Comunity Central - A wiki for all Wikians!
items.desc: Looking for help or advice? Community Central is home for all on FANDOM!  Join us here to meet other editors, chat with FANDOM staff and learn tips & tricks for editing on your community. On Community Central you will find our helpful community forum, staff blog, help pages and many other support materials. So stop by to meet and learn from others!

items.name: L5r: Legend of the Five Rings Wiki
items.title: L5r: Legend of the Five Rings Wiki
items.headline: L5R Wiki
items.desc: Legend of the Five Rings Wiki is a database for Legend of the Five Rings (often abbreviated "L5R"), a fictional setting that covers in detail the fantastical land of Rokugan, a nation whose culture and history is based on that of feudal Japan. The setting also briefly touches upon many of the different cultures that occupy the same world. This world is the foundation for the Legend of the Five Rings Collectible Card Game, the Legend of the Five Rings Role-Playing Game, the Clan Wars miniatures game, and a series of novels.

items.name: Google Wiki
items.title: Google Wiki
items.headline: Learn about Google's services, products, tips and tricks at the Google Wiki
items.desc: The Google Wiki is a place where users can research and learn things about Google, write about it, and even chat about it! We have information on all parts of Google, from when they very first began, to things they're planning on doing in the future, to some of their smallest, yet fascinating acts that people rarely hear about! It's also a blast to come on and share things you found out about Google that others haven't heard of yet. You can enjoy the fun of having other users comment on your findings! Come and help build another awesome wiki about an awesome subject, and have a blast while you're doing it.

items.name: Constructed Worlds Wiki
items.title: Constructed Worlds Wiki
items.headline: Constructed Worlds Wiki
items.desc: Conworlding, also called worldbuilding, is the process of constructing an imaginary world, sometimes associated with a whole fictional universe. If you've ever wanted to create a powerful hi-tech nation or a tribe of primative warriors, then the Conworlds Wiki is for you! We don't discriminate and we welcome all!

items.name: Consumer Information
items.title: Consumer Information
items.headline: Consumer Information Wiki
items.desc: This wiki is dedicated to the information personal and small business shoppers in English-speaking countries (Great Britain, USA, Canada, Australia) need to spend their money wisely. You can read facts, reviews and links related to specific products, brands and retailers, learn about general product types, including definitions and buying guides, and find general guides to topics such as birthday and holiday gift selection and online shopping without a credit card.

items.name: Apple Wiki
items.title: Apple Wiki
items.headline: Join the Apple Wiki!
items.desc: The Apple Wiki is the ultimate place for information on anything Apple. You can learn about the iPod, iPhone, iPad, and Apple computers. We got biographies about Steve Jobs, Tim Cook, and everyone else. We list every feature from Apple products. Best of all you can add what you know to the wiki. Join today!

items.name: Palk Bay and Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project
items.title: Palk Bay and Sethusamudram Shipping Canal Project

items.name: RangerWiki
items.title: RangerWiki
items.headline: Welcome to RangerWiki!
items.desc: The Super Sentai and Power Rangers Wiki

items.name: Pro Wrestling
items.title: Pro Wrestling
items.headline: Welcome to the Professional Wrestling Wiki!
items.desc: The Pro Wrestling Wiki is a collaborative project to create a dynamic resource for information on professional wrestling. It is a place to find general information about all your favorite professional wrestling promotions and personalities, past and present. Read about the latest in matches, T.V. episodes, tag teams, merchandise and more!

items.name: Mittelalter Wiki
items.title: Mittelalter Wiki
items.headline: Das Mittelalter Wiki stellt sich vor.
items.desc: Das Mittelalter Wiki ist ein Projekt von und für alle Interessierten am Thema Mittelalter und Reenactment. Es dient als Enzyklopädie für Beschreibungen historischer Tatsachen und ebenso als Plattform für historische Darstellung im Rahmen experimenteller Archäologie und lebendiger Geschichte. Dieses Wikia bietet außerdem Raum für die Vorstellung von mittelalterlichen Vereinen, Händlern und Künstlern, sowie Linksammlungen zu historischen Veranstaltungen, Internetseiten, Museen, Büchern, Dokumentationen und anderen Quellen, die sich mit diesen Themen befassen. Interessierte Nutzer sind daher eingeladen, sich an diesem Projekt zu beteiligen und mitzuhelfen dieses Wiki auszugestalten.

items.name: RuneScape Wiki
items.title: RuneScape Wiki
items.headline: The RuneScape Wiki
items.desc:
Started in April of 2005, the RuneScape Wiki's goal is to remain a vast, knowledgeable source for all things in RuneScape.

The RuneScape Wiki aims to be a competitor to all major RuneScape fansites. Guides to new quests or holiday events, for example, can be made in under an hour, far ahead of other fansites.

It contains a guide to every quest and treasure trail, and over 26,000 articles about items, locations and monsters.


RuneScape is copyright 1999 - 2014 Jagex Ltd. The RuneScape Wiki is in no way affiliated with Jagex.

items.name: Law and Order
items.title: Law and Order
items.headline: Law and Order Wiki
items.desc: Law and Order Wiki is a collaborative database for the Law and Order universe. The wiki contains information about the original Law and Order series as well as its spin-offs: Law and Order: SVU, Criminal Intent, Trial by Jury, UK, Los Angeles, and other related media releases.

items.name: Memory Beta, non-canon Star Trek Wiki
items.title: Memory Beta, non-canon Star Trek Wiki
items.headline: Memory Beta
items.desc: Memory Beta is an encyclopedia of non-canonical Star Trek information, including novels, comic books, RPG sourcebooks, video games and any other licensed works. Read about culture, characters, technology, starships, and more.

items.name: EverQuest 2 Wiki
items.title: EverQuest 2 Wiki
items.headline: EQ2i
items.desc: EQ2i is an award-winning wiki about the MMORPG EverQuest 2 by Sony Online Entertainment, featuring nearly 60,000 pages on a wide variety of topics, such as quests, equipment, items, monsters, NPCs, and zones.

items.name: Hitchhikers
items.title: Hitchhikers
items.headline: Welcome to the Hitchhiker wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to Hitchhikers Wiki!  A wiki dedicated to the truly amazing works of Douglas Adams and Eoin Colfer that anyone can edit. 

First published as a comedic radio series in 1978 Douglas Adams series became an international multi-media phenomenon. His trilogy in six-parts has received acclaim through the years, the last being written by Eoin Colfer. 

Many other adaptations from the original radio series has seen as Radio and TV Series as well as comic book adaptations. And in later years saw the development of a Film and Computer Game.

items.name: Nickelodeon
items.title: Nickelodeon
items.headline: Nickipedia, the Nickelodeon Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to Nickipedia, the Nickelodeon Wiki that anyone can edit, including you! Nickipedia is a fan-made Nickelodeon information database collaboration. We are not affiliated with Nickelodeon, but we are a comprehensive resource for everything to do with Nickelodeon. If you're a fan and want to share your knowledge and passion, join us today!

items.name: Disney Wiki
items.title: Disney Wiki
items.headline: Over 23,000 pages and we keep moving forward by editing every day!
items.desc: The Disney Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia for everything related to Walt Disney and his work. Here you can find, create, and edit articles on Disney theme parks, film companies, television networks, films, and characters. Discover more than ever before about popular franchises through Mickey Mouse, The Lion King, Aladdin, Phineas and Ferb, Gravity Falls, Wreck-It Ralph, The Disney Afternoon, One Saturday Morning, Kingdom Hearts, Pirates of the Caribbean, Marvel Comics, Star Wars and plenty of Pixar favorites!

items.name: Artemis Fowl
items.title: Artemis Fowl
items.headline: Welcome to the Artemis Fowl Wikia!
items.desc: Artemis Fowl is a teen fantasy novel written by Irish author Eoin Colfer. It is the first book in the Artemis Fowl series, and is followed by Artemis Fowl: The Arctic Incident. Described by its author as "Die Hard with fairies", it follows the adventures of 12-year-old Artemis Fowl, a criminal mastermind. Throughout the book, the third-person narration switches repeatedly from following the human characters to various fairy characters.

items.name: White Wolf
items.title: White Wolf
items.headline: White Wolf Wiki
items.desc: The White Wolf Wiki is a collaborative encyclopedia project where you can find out about the worlds and systems created by White Wolf, the producer of many roleplaying games, board games, card games, novels and more. The wiki regularly updates their content with latest and upcoming releases for all White Wolf games.

items.name: Sciences de la Vie et de la Terre
items.title: Sciences de la Vie et de la Terre

items.name: Eberron Wiki
items.title: Eberron Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Eberron Wiki!
items.desc: This wiki was created with the intention of creating a complete and readily available repository of fan-based information about the Eberron Campaign Setting developed by Wizards of the Coast and Keith Baker. The World of Eberron consists of a number of features for the Eberron campaign setting for the Dungeons & Dragons fantasy role-playing game.

items.name: RollerCoaster Tycoon
items.title: RollerCoaster Tycoon
items.headline: Take a ride on the Rollercoaster Tycoon Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to RollerCoaster Tycoon Wiki, a RollerCoaster Tycoon database that anyone can edit.

RollerCoaster Tycoon is a successful video game franchise, first developed by Chris Sawyer and MicroProse and distributed through Hasbro Interactive. The first game in the franchise, RollerCoaster Tycoon, was later followed by multiple expansions and two sequel games, developed either by Sawyer himself or with Sawyer on-board as Executive Producer. The latest sequel in the franchise, RollerCoaster Tycoon 3, was released in 2004.

items.name: DC Animated Universe
items.title: DC Animated Universe
items.headline: DC Animated Universe Wiki
items.desc: DC Animated Wiki is devoted to the DC Animated Universe. It provides extensive coverage of everything pertaining to the line of DC-based shows, which started with Batman: The Animated Series in 1992 and concluded with Justice League Unlimited in 2006.

items.name: MMKB
items.title: MMKB
items.headline: Mega Man Knowledge Database
items.desc: Mega Man Knowledge Database is a community site for the Mega Man video game series. The wiki contains all information related to the franchise, such as the games, characters, enemies, items, cartoons, anime, comics, manga, and more.

items.name: Teletraan I: The Transformers Wiki
items.title: Teletraan I: The Transformers Wiki
items.headline: Transformers Wiki
items.desc: Transformers Wiki is a knowledge base devoted to the Transformers franchise, covering the TV series, comic books, Entertainment, real-life people, objects, technology, planets, and anything else related to Transformers.

items.name: Sharpe
items.title: Sharpe
items.desc: Welcome to the Sharpe's Wiki, a reference resource to the twenty-one novels and three short stories by Bernard Cornwell featuring Richard Sharpe, as well as the television movies based upon them.

items.name: Counter-Strike Wiki
items.title: Counter-Strike Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Counter-Strike Wiki
items.desc: The wiki devoted to the Counter-Strike series that anyone can edit.

items.name: Beer Wiki
items.title: Beer Wiki
items.headline: Thirsty For Knowledge about Beer? If so Welcome to the Beer Wiki.
items.desc: If you love beer, Beer Wiki in the place for you. Browse to find information on many individual beers, types of beer, breweries, the brewing process, and more.

items.name: Zeldapedia
items.title: Zeldapedia
items.headline: Zeldapedia
items.desc: Zeldapedia's goal is to become the best source of information for Nintendo's Legend of Zelda series. Since its creation in 2005, Zeldapedia has grown into a large, community-based wiki and has been translated into several languages.

items.name: Full House
items.title: Full House
items.headline: Welcome to the Full House Wiki
items.desc: A collaborative website about the 1987-95 American sitcom Full House

items.name: Left Space
items.title: Left Space
items.headline: Welcome to the Leftpedia
items.desc: Optimism about the possibility of improving living conditions for everyone in America so that every individual can realize their full human potential is at the heart of the democratic Left tradition in America. Against the ideological Right's grinding negativity and appeals to the fear, selfishness and ignorance, the democratic Left offers hope for national renewal.

items.name: Saturday Night Live Wiki
items.title: Saturday Night Live Wiki
items.headline: Live from new York, it's the Saturday Night Live Wiki!
items.desc:
Saturday Night Live is an American late-night live sketch comedy show created by Lorne Michaels and Dick Ebersol, beginning as NBC's Saturday Night on October 11, 1975. The show revolves around sketches parodying current events, American culture, and politics.
Every episode has a "host", who is a celebrity guest starring on the show, as well as a musical guest, although a host can be both. At the beginning, a cold open sketch is preformed ending with someone breaking character and usually blurting "Live from New York, it's Saturday Night!". (This cold opening was removed for season 8, but quickly returned.) Additional sketches include Weekend Update, which functions as a new show, a digital short, and commercial parodies.

items.name: Puzzle Pirates
items.title: Puzzle Pirates
items.headline: Visit Puzzle Pirates Wiki!
items.desc: Puzzle Pirates Wiki is the unofficial wiki for Yohoho Puzzle Pirates, and is a free-content encyclopedia, written collaboratively by Yohoho! Puzzle Pirates players from around the world. The site is a wiki, which means that anyone can edit articles simply by clicking on the edit this page link. Visit it today, and create your own pirate page =]

items.name: Bomberman Wiki
items.title: Bomberman Wiki
items.headline: Blast it up with Bomberman Wiki!
items.desc: Like competing with other people by blowing each other up with explosives? Then head on over to Bomberman Wiki! This is the largest database for all things Bomberman! You can help us by expanding the wiki articles with your knowledge. Bomberman Wiki contains various information about characters, items, games, books and manuals, and the anime!

items.name: Atheism
items.title: Atheism
items.headline: Welcome to the Atheism Wikia!
items.desc: This is a Wikia for Atheists and people curious about Atheism. People often assume that Atheism is a religion, which it is not. Saying that atheism is a religion is rather like saying not collecting coins is a hobby. Atheists are often associated with scientific thinking and Critical thinking, while religions demand belief without supporting empirical evidence. Scientists such as Richard Dawkins have shown how scientific thinking leads to atheism.

items.name: Last Exile
items.title: Last Exile
items.headline: Take to the skies at the Last Exile Wikia
items.desc: Last Exile (ラストエグザイル, Rasuto Eguzairu) is a Japanese animated television series created by Gonzo. It featured a production team led by director Koichi Chigira, character designer Range Murata, and production designer Mahiro Maeda. The three had previously worked together in Blue Submarine No. 6, one of the first CG anime series. Last Exile premiered on TV Tokyo on April 7, 2003 and ran for twenty-six episodes until its conclusion on September 29, 2003.

items.name: Désencyclopédie
items.title: Désencyclopédie
items.headline: Le pastiche de Wikipédia
items.desc: Le contenu de la dÉsencyclopédie, le site lui-même et les administrateurs du site sont une immense parodie sans queue ni tête à la sexualité douteuse et à l'hygiène approximative. Si vous prenez au sérieux un traître mot de ce qui est écrit, vous êtes encore plus con que vous en avez l'air.

items.name: WoWWiki
items.title: WoWWiki
items.headline: WoWWiki, the original Warcraft wiki
items.desc: WoWWiki is a wiki dedicated to cataloging the Warcraft universe (with a focus, though not priority, on World of Warcraft); covering the entire Warcraft series of games, RPG reference books, strategy guides, trading card games, comics, novels, and short stories. Get up to date on the latest World of Warcraft expansion! Look up that epic item or recipe. Share tips and tricks.

items.name: Academic Publishing Wiki
items.title: Academic Publishing Wiki
items.headline: Hello, and welcome to the Academic Publishing Wikia!
items.desc: This project is meant to give people with original ideas a means of obtaining peer review and constructive criticism, and also to publish these ideas in wiki format for the free use timbangan digital and benefit of others. Works can first be placed in wiki format as an initial draft and marked for inclusion in the critical peer review process. With successful passage through this stage, the article can then be included in an academic journal fitting of it.

items.name: Warhammer 40k
items.title: Warhammer 40k
items.headline: Warhammer 40,000 Wiki
items.desc:
"It is the 41st Millennium. For more than a hundred centuries the Emperor of Mankind has sat immobile on the Golden Throne of Earth. He is the master of mankind by the will of the gods and master of a million worlds by the might of his inexhaustible armies. He is a rotting carcass writhing invisibly with power from the Dark Age of Technology. He is the Carrion Lord of the vast Imperium of Man for whom a thousand souls are sacrificed every day so that he may never truly die.Yet even in his deathless state, the Emperor continues his eternal vigilance. Mighty battlefleets cross the daemon-infested miasma of the Warp, the only route between distant stars, their way lit by the Astronomican, the psychic manifestation of the Emperor's will. Vast armies give battle in His name on uncounted worlds. Greatest amongst his soldiers are the Adeptus Astartes, the Space Marines, bio-engineered super-warriors. Their comrades in arms are legion: the Imperial Guard and countless planetary defence forces, the ever-vigilant Inquisition and the tech-priests of the Adeptus Mechanicus to name only a few. But for all their multitudes, they are barely enough to hold off the ever-present threat to humanity from aliens, heretics, mutants -- and far, far worse. To be a man in such times is to be one amongst untold billions. It is to live in the cruelest and most bloody regime imaginable. These are the tales of those times. Forget the power of technology and science, for so much has been forgotten, never to be relearned. Forget the promise of progress and understanding, for in the grim dark future there is only war. There is no peace amongst the stars, only an eternity of carnage and slaughter, and the laughter of thirsting gods." 

Warhammer 40k Wiki is a collaborative project to create the most definitive and accurate reference for everything related to the Warhammer 40,000 universe.

items.name: Endurance Wiki
items.title: Endurance Wiki
items.headline: Test your endurance on the Endurance Wikia
items.desc: The Endurance Wikia community site was founded by fans of the game show and television series Endurance. The community attempts to detail information about every contestant and every episode in this series.  We are always looking for new contributors who are fans of this show - so if this is you, please feel free to help us improve our Wikia.

items.name: Harry Potter Wiki
items.title: Harry Potter Wiki
items.headline: Harry Potter Wiki
items.desc: Harry Potter Wiki is a collaborative knowledge base about the widely-popular series by J. K. Rowling, including the books, movies, characters, and much more. Join the active community and share your enthusiasm for Harry Potter.

items.name: Turtledove
items.title: Turtledove
items.headline: Welcome to the Harry Turtledove Wiki
items.desc: The Harry Turtledove Wiki is an encyclopedia of people, places, and events that are portrayed in the writings of Harry Turtledove, famed author in the genre of alternate history. These articles can include information about both the historical person and the alternate version(s) Turtledove creates in his fantastic stories. We also have articles on his novels, stories and other writings -- he's written numerous works of historical fiction, fantasy, and science fiction in addition to his alternate history works.

items.name: Gojipedia
items.title: Gojipedia
items.headline: Learn about Godzilla at Wikizilla!
items.desc: Gojipedia is a collaborative wiki project dedicated to documenting all things related to Godzilla, Toho, Gamera, alongside other popular Kaiju, or giant monsters! We invite you to join Gojipedia to help us make it the best, most comprehensive Godzilla informational site on the internet!

items.name: X-Files Wiki
items.title: X-Files Wiki
items.headline: The X-Files Wiki
items.desc: The X-Files Wiki is a community database that gives all the details, information, data, and facts about The X-Files universe with episode summaries, character biographies, conspiracies, weapons, artifacts, and of course, aliens and paranormal activities. This wiki also gives information from the television series Millennium and The Lone Gunmen. Read about the mysteries of paranormal activities and follow the X-Files unit as they uncover The Truth.

items.name: Honorverse
items.title: Honorverse
items.headline: Welcome to the Honorverse Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Honorverse Wiki, an encyclopedia of David Weber's Honor Harringon Universe, which includes books, reference materials, and games. All pages can be edited by anyone, including you! If you're a fan of the Honorverse, join the wiki and share your knowledge and passion with your fellow fans!

items.name: The eWrestling Encyclopedia
items.title: The eWrestling Encyclopedia
items.headline: Welcome to the eWrestling Encyclopedia!
items.desc:
The eWrestling Encyclopedia is the first fully interactive e-wrestling knowledge base. It was formed in July of 2005, and is hosted by Wikia.
As an editable website, EWE is a collaborative attempt to document the past, present and future of everything related to the 'hobby' of e-wrestling. This includes information on the characters, federations, inter-federations and handlers and anything which can be written about to an acceptable level.

The eWrestling Encyclopedia strives to change the face of e-wrestling, and to prevent the inevitable situation where the stars of today will be forgotten in ten years time. We plan to become an indispensable tool to all handlers and e-federation fanatics, and with your help, we might be able to do just that.

items.name: Wikivex - The Free, Online, Vexillium Encyclopedia
items.title: Wikivex - The Free, Online, Vexillium Encyclopedia

items.name: Toastmasters International
items.title: Toastmasters International
items.headline: Welcome to the Toastmasters Wiki
items.desc: Toastmasters International is an organization dedicated to communication and leadership development. The Toastmasters Wiki is dedicated to the Toastmasters everywhere who improve their speaking and leadership skills by attending one of the 13,500 clubs in 116 countries that make up their global network. Enter to learn more!

items.name: New Democratic Party of Canada Wiki
items.title: New Democratic Party of Canada Wiki

items.name: Moviepedia
items.title: Moviepedia
items.headline: Welcome to Moviepedia
items.desc: Welcome to Moviepedia, an encyclopedic site of information on past, present, and future movies! Updated by fans, Moviepedia is a work in process, but it is sure to hold the latest information about upcoming releases that you might be interested in! Enter now to learn more about what you can do to help!

items.name: Baseball Wiki
items.title: Baseball Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Baseball Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to Baseball Wikia! Baseball Wikia is the free baseball encyclopedia that anyone can edit. Baseball Wikia has articles about almost anything that's related to the sport, baseball, from Minor League Baseball to Major League Baseball, from baseball players to baseball coaches and managers, from baseball stadiums to the history of baseball, and much more! items.name: Adobe Premiere Pro
items.title: Adobe Premiere Pro
items.headline: Get Help with Adobe Premiere Pro
items.desc:
Having a problem with Adobe Premiere Pro?  You've come to the right place, we can help you trouble shoot the issues.

Some Quick Tips
    Remove all Adobe beta software installed on your computer. For CS4 see here. For CS3 see here. 

    Ensure your OS is set to display at least 32bit color. Lower display settings are known to cause problems. 

    If you are using more than one monitor, switch to using only one monitor while troubleshooting. 

    Open Premiere pro and load a default workspace, for example Window > Workspace > Edit. Then choose Window > Workspace > Reset workspace name, where workspace name is the name of the workspace you loaded. 

    Check your scratch disk settings, especially the Media Cache. If Premiere Pro is trying to use a disk that is no longer accessible, or a directory (folder) that is read-only, it causes strange problems. Do not use network drives. 

    Check that you have more than 20% of free disk space remaining on every hard drive.

items.name: Xenosaga Wiki
items.title: Xenosaga Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Xenosaga Wiki
items.desc: Were are a wiki dedicated to the science-fiction, Role-Playing-Game series, Xenosaga, developed by Monolith Soft and published by Namco. The series currently consists of three main games with three spin-offs, as well as an animated series. Come join us and read all about it!

items.name: Encyclopedia Hiigara
items.title: Encyclopedia Hiigara
items.headline: Welcome to the Encyclopedia Hiigara Wiki!
items.desc:
Encyclopedia Hiigara (short: EH, also known as Homeworld Wiki) is largest Homeworld encyclopedia, created by fans for fans of Homeworld universe. The first notes about Encyclopedia Hiigara come from March 2004, when Ishaar Niirfa created detailed fanon description of several factions in Homeworld Universe, including Hiigaran Federation, Taiidan Imperium, and more. These were first such detailed descriptions of factions, and soon become great source of inspiration for many fans of Homeworld. Encyclopedia Hiigara however, soon become much more, wiki project created by Ishaar under little changed nick by Niirfa-sa. 

Join our wiki and help us maintain the encyclopedia!

items.name: Trailer Park Wiki
items.title: Trailer Park Wiki
items.headline: Come to the Trailer Park!
items.desc: The Trailer Park WIki is all about the popular Canadian Television and movie franchise, Trailer Park Boys! We've been around since 2009, but we are staking a new claim as the hub of information for everyone interested in the show. Come on out, get drunk with us and have a few laughs. We are looking for experiences writers and admins as well to make this a great place to hang out. See you there!

items.name: James Bond Wiki
items.title: James Bond Wiki
items.headline: A true information goldmine about the world's greatest spy, James Bond.
items.desc: Bond... James Bond. The world's great spy since 1953. First penned by Ian Fleming in the novel "Casino Royale", the legendary 007 has appeared in 39 official novels (14 by Fleming) and 24 films over the past 60+ years. The James Bond Wikia has chronicled the novel, video game, and cinematic adventures from 1953's "Casino Royale" to the newest instalment, 2015's "Spectre".

items.name: Ren & Stimpy Wiki
items.title: Ren & Stimpy Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Ren & Stimpy Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to Ren & Stimpy Wiki, the collective database about the Nickelodeon television series The Ren & Stimpy Show that anyone can edit! 

The Ren & Stimpy Show, often simply Ren & Stimpy, is an American animated television series, created by Canadian animator John Kricfalusi for Nickelodeon. The series focuses on the titular characters: Ren Höek, a psychotic chihuahua, and Stimpson J. Cat, a good-natured, dimwitted cat. The show officially premiered on August 11, 1991, later the same day as the debut of Rugrats and Doug, the three of which comprised the original Nicktoons. The show ran for five seasons on the network, ending its original run with the Christmas episode "A Scooter for Yaksmas." The show was rated TV-Y7 on Nickelodeon/Nicktoons, and TV-PG on the Spike TV repeats.

items.name: VereinsWiki

items.desc: Das Vereins-Wiki ist eine freie Enzyklopädie für Vereine, Vereinsmitglieder, Spieler, Parteien, Sportarten, Datensammlungen, Vereins-KnowHow und Sportler nach Vorbild der Wikipedia, zu der jeder mit seinem Wissen beitragen kann. items.name: Lemony Snicket Wiki
items.title: Lemony Snicket Wiki

items.desc: Welcome to the Lemony Snicket Wiki, a wiki dedicated to A SERIES OF UNFORTUNATE EVENTS, ALL THE WRONG QUESTIONS, and other wretched works by LEMONY SNICKET. Read up on the books, the Netflix series, characters, and more on our wiki! We welcome new users to come and contribute to the wiki. The world is quiet here.

items.name: Comic Book Series
items.title: Comic Book Series
items.headline: Welcome to the Comic Book Series Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Comic Book Series Wiki. The goal of this Wiki is to introduce you to on-going comic book series that you might have trouble understanding if you were to just go into a shop and pick up the latest issue.

items.name: Metal Gear Wiki
items.title: Metal Gear Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Metal Gear Wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to the Metal Gear Wiki, your resource for all things Metal Gear! The Metal Gear Wiki is the ultimate resource of knowledge for the Metal Gear video game franchise. In addition to all canonical and non-canonical games, the wiki also covers remakes, updates, Entertainment, and even the people who develop the games.

items.name: Wikitroid
items.title: Wikitroid
items.headline: Wikitroid
items.desc: Metroid Wiki "Wikitroid" is a  community-run database that aims to create the best resource for Metroid, a series of video games produced by Nintendo. The Metroid games chronicle the missions of bounty hunter Samus Aran in a science fiction setting which contains many similarities to the Alien film franchise. The wiki has nearly 3500 pages of content devoted to the game series.

items.name: WoWWiki
items.title: WoWWiki
items.headline: WOWWiki
items.desc: Das deutsche WoWWiki ist die Anlaufstelle für alles Wissenswerte zum MMORPG World of Warcraft. Ob du Völker, Klassen, Berufe, Gebiete, Dungeons oder Raids suchst, hier wirst du fündig! Außerdem stellen wir jeden Monat herausragende Artikel vor, bieten interessante Umfragen an und bauen unser WoWWiki immer weiter aus. Mit der Veröffentlichung der Erweiterung "Battle for Azeroth" wird es wieder viele Neuerungen, Gebiete und Charaktere geben, die als Seiten im WoWWiki verewigt werden sollen. Willst auch du dabei mithelfen, das WoWWiki noch größer zu machen? Dann schau vorbei und tob dich aus!

items.name: Dune
items.title: Dune
items.headline: Want to know everything about Herbert's "Dune"?
items.desc:
The "Dune Wiki" is dedicated to the famous, elaborate universe created by Frank Herbert; an interstellar empire fledged in feuds, conspiracies, intrigues and exotic technologies. Herbert's world spawned movies, games, an encyclopedia and new book series.

The Dune Wiki features three portals that allow space for the several incarnations of the Dune universe. The universe created by Herbert; the expanded universe from the Dune Encyclopedia; and the events expanded by the new books.

items.name: Inheriwiki
items.title: Inheriwiki
items.headline: Inheriwiki, the Inheritance Cycle Wiki
items.desc: The Inheritance Wiki (Inheriwiki) is dedicated to The Inheritance Cycle (previously known as the Inheritance Trilogy), a series of high-fantasy novels by homeschooled author Christopher Paolini. The series follows the exploits of Eragon, a teenage orphan who becomes the first of a new order of Dragon Riders. It covers the detailed Universe of the Cycle, written in in-universe style, and also real-world actors, authors and topics connected to the Cycle.
